<paragraph id="D20C3697FFD8FFF4A2977B9E957B0AAC" blockId="17.[926,1307,196,221]" box="[926,1307,196,221]" pageId="17" pageNumber="1229">
<heading id="894481FBFFD8FFF4A2977B9E957B0AAC" box="[926,1307,196,221]" centered="true" fontSize="9" level="2" pageId="17" pageNumber="1229" reason="8">
FAMILY 
<taxonomicName id="15B34D14FFD8FFF4A2F27B9E957B0AAC" authority="HOYLE, 1886" authorityName="Hoyle" authorityYear="1886" box="[1019,1307,196,221]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Gonatidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Oegopsida" pageId="17" pageNumber="1229" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">
GONATIDAE 
<bibRefCitation id="B6224B66FFD8FFF4A58E7B9E957B0AAC" author="Hoyle WE" box="[1159,1307,196,221]" pageId="17" pageNumber="1229" pagination="1 - 245" refId="ref15068" refString="Hoyle WE. 1886. Report on the Cephalopods collected by H. M. S. Challenger during the years 1873 - 1876. Zoology 16: 1 - 245." type="journal article" year="1886">HOYLE, 1886</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D20C3697FFD8FFF4A2BA7BB095670B72" blockId="17.[947,1287,234,259]" box="[947,1287,234,259]" pageId="17" pageNumber="1229">(19 SPECIES IN FOUR GENERA)</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9AA9651CFFD8FFF4A2207A4E94A90900" pageId="17" pageNumber="1229" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="D20C3697FFD8FFF4A2207A4E9403084C" blockId="17.[809,1425,275,573]" pageId="17" pageNumber="1229">
<emphasis id="E0C7EA85FFD8FFF4A2207A4E93C30B58" box="[809,931,276,297]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="1229">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Medium adult-sized muscular 
<taxonomicName id="15B34D14FFD8FFF4A4117A4995F10B58" authorityName="D' ORBIGNY" authorityYear="1845" box="[1304,1425,275,297]" class="Cephalopoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Oegopsida" pageId="17" pageNumber="1229" phylum="Mollusca" rank="order">Oegopsida</taxonomicName>
with buccal connectives attached to the ventral borders of ventral arms; with four series of arm suckers, usually with hooks in the two medial series of dorsal, dorsolateral and ventrolateral arms; tentacles with numerous irregular series of suckers, sometimes with hooks, funnel–mantle locking apparatus straight, reaching the anterior margin of the mantle; usually without photophores; gladius with primary conus; egg masses brooded by females.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D20C3697FFD8FFF4A220793C94A90900" blockId="17.[809,1426,614,881]" pageId="17" pageNumber="1229">
<emphasis id="E0C7EA85FFD8FFF4A220793C93F7080A" box="[809,919,614,635]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="1229">Remarks:</emphasis>
This family has a wide range of variation within several key characters. The genera 
<taxonomicName id="15B34D14FFD8FFF4A42479DF93C208C9" authority="Gray, 1849" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1849" class="Cephalopoda" family="Gonatidae" genus="Gonatus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Oegopsida" pageId="17" pageNumber="1229" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="E0C7EA85FFD8FFF4A42479DF95F008EB" box="[1325,1424,645,666]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="1229">Gonatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="B6224B66FFD8FFF4A22079F993C208C9" author="Gray JE" box="[809,930,675,696]" pageId="17" pageNumber="1229" refId="ref14816" refString="Gray JE. 1849. Catalogue of the Mollusca in the collection of the British Museum. Part I. Cephalopoda Artepedia. London: Trustees of the British Museum." type="book" year="1849">Gray, 1849</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="15B34D14FFD8FFF4A2D079FE94B808C9" authority="Nesis, 1972" authorityName="Nesis" authorityYear="1972" box="[985,1240,675,697]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Gonatidae" genus="Eogonatus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Oegopsida" pageId="17" pageNumber="1229" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="E0C7EA85FFD8FFF4A2D079FE943108C8" box="[985,1105,676,697]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="1229">Eogonatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="B6224B66FFD8FFF4A55F79F994B808C9" author="Nesis KN" box="[1110,1240,675,697]" pageId="17" pageNumber="1229" pagination="1300 - 1307" refId="ref16142" refString="Nesis KN. 1972. Two new species of gonatid squids from the north Pacific. Zoologicheskii Zhurnal 51: 1300 - 1307." type="journal article" year="1972">Nesis, 1972</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
have a modified carpal locking apparatus with elongated ridges, suckers and knobs at the base of the manus. The genus 
<taxonomicName id="15B34D14FFD8FFF4A22079A594230965" authority="Naef, 1921" authorityName="Naef" authorityYear="1921" box="[809,1091,767,789]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Gonatidae" genus="Berryteuthis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Oegopsida" pageId="17" pageNumber="1229" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="E0C7EA85FFD8FFF4A22079A593DC0965" box="[809,956,767,788]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="1229">Berryteuthis</emphasis>
Naef, 1921
</taxonomicName>
has no hooks on tentacular clubs, whereas 
<taxonomicName id="15B34D14FFD8FFF4A2E27844957F0942" authority="Sasaki, 1920" authorityName="Sasaki" authorityYear="1920" box="[1003,1311,798,820]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Gonatidae" genus="Gonatopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Oegopsida" pageId="17" pageNumber="1229" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="E0C7EA85FFD8FFF4A2E2784494140942" box="[1003,1140,798,819]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="1229">Gonatopsis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="B6224B66FFD8FFF4A5767844957F0942" author="Sasaki M" box="[1151,1311,798,820]" pageId="17" pageNumber="1229" pagination="163 - 203" refId="ref16935" refString="Sasaki M. 1920. Report on cephalopods collected during 1906 by the United States Bureau of Fisheries steamer &quot; Albatross &quot; in the northwestern Pacific. Proceedings of the United States National Museum 57: 163 - 203." type="journal article" year="1920">Sasaki, 1920</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
loses its tentacles in the early juvenile stage. 
<taxonomicName id="15B34D14FFD8FFF4A5ED786793D30901" authority="Young, 1972" authorityName="Young" authorityYear="1972" class="Cephalopoda" family="Gonatidae" genus="Gonatus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Oegopsida" pageId="17" pageNumber="1229" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="pyrus">
<emphasis id="E0C7EA85FFD8FFF4A5ED786795F20923" box="[1252,1426,829,850]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="1229">Gonatus pyrus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="B6224B66FFD8FFF4A220780193D30901" author="Young RE" box="[809,947,859,880]" pageId="17" pageNumber="1229" refId="ref18046" refString="Young RE. 1972. The systematics and areal distribution of pelagic cephalopods from the seas off Southern California. Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology, 97. Washington: Smithsonian Institution Scholarly Press." type="book" year="1972">Young, 1972</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
has ocular photophores.
</paragraph>
